```suggestion
instance (priority := 100) SubsemiringClass.nonUnitalSubsemiringClass (S : Type*)
    (R : Type u) [NonAssocSemiring R] [SetLike S R] [SubsemiringClass S R] :
```
This was actually a bad definition as originally written because `Module ‚ÑÇ M` was a duplicated instance leading to multiple `SMul` structures on this type.
This declaration got a *lot* slower (I believe, in part, because there is now a `Analysis.Complex.Basic` transitive import), but I had trouble tracing it down. Squeezing the `simp`s fixed it though.
I suspect, but I'm not positive, that this synth pending issue will no longer plague stuff involving `Unitization`. I checked that this comment is no longer necessary.
